text: Oneida is a city in Nemaha County, Kansas, United States. As of the 2020 census, 61 people lived there. == History == Oneida was planned out about 1873. It was named after the Oneida people. The town's streets were named after the main thoroughfares of Chicago. == Geography == Oneida is at (39.866799, -95.93982).
